<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-88-0021 </DOCNO><TEXT>90% of Australian export coal is carried to the ports by rail. In NewSouth Wales transport and port charges plus royalties represent about30% of the cost of shipping a tonne of coal; in Queensland it is 34%.Rail freight rates have been reduced but it is argued that this is sofar insufficient. Recommendations are made concerning pricing policyand for improving rail efficiency. Competition in rail transport is alsorecommended. The use of pipelines to transport coal is considered.</TEXT></DOC>